    "Regarding long essay-type descriptive answers, ChatGPT did not go beyond the length limit of 1000-1200 words, even after the prompt was fine-tuned to specify to answer the questions in at least 3000 words.",
    "ChatGPT responded negatively when asked whether it has any word limits for a single response.",
    "However, the issue of a smaller number of words also persisted in subsequent attempts.",
    "Discussion Principal FindingsIn this study, ChatGPT scored 72.3% on paper 1 and 61% on paper 2, while the mean scores of the students were 43% and 45%, respectively.",
    "The responses of ChatGPT were also rated to be satisfactorily relevant (88%), coherent (90%), and complete (80%) for most of the questions."
